Cypress on-call wrap-up for Jan 27-31:
Summary: started off calm and reasonable but then things really broke :disappointed: but hopefully we're through the woods now
• https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CSY11CK7T/p1738189106141459
    ◦ TableList to TableGrid update in FileList and a boolean condition bug broke some tests
    ◦ The latter got fixed, the former test is skipped, and the fix is pending Cypress CI :sweat_smile:
•  https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CSY11CK7T/p1738253372002599
    ◦ job-service broke due to db migration, but fixed the next day from a new deployment
    ◦ Cypress sandboxes were spun up with an outdated script, but was fixed when we changed the snapshot
• Lots of failures today likely due to a job-service backlog that needed to be processed, causing a lot of test timeouts
    ◦ But I think we might be getting through it now? I just had a success (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/17296/overview?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1)!
    ◦ It should alleviate itself over the weekend when we don't have as much traffic too
